In the call graph viewer below, each node is a function belonging to this package and its children are the functions it calls—perhaps dynamically.

The root nodes are the entry points of the package: functions that may be called from outside the package. There may be non-exported or anonymous functions among them if they are called dynamically from another package.

Click a node to visit that function's source code. From there you can visit its callers by clicking its declaring func token.

    Provides 245 strong-typed hooks for your own custom handler functions to be invoked when the Walk() method is called on any instance of any (non-attribute-related) struct type defined in this package. If your custom handler does get called at all for a given struct instance, then it always gets called twice, first with the 'enter' bool argument set to true, then (after having Walk()ed all subordinate struct instances, if any) once again with it set to false.
